ck window is correctly interpreted (should it be 30 trading days before 2024-06-07, or calendar days?), (3) whether the 'surge within 10 days after low-volume period ends' allows the surge to occur after 2024-06-07 or must be within the cutoff date.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"issue\": \"My implementation limits analysis to first 100 stocks (chinext_stocks[:100]) which may miss valid matches in the remaining ~1000 ChiNext stocks\",\n      \"severity\": \"medium\",\n      \"affected_agents\": [\"claudecode\"],\n      \"recommendation\": \"Remove the [:100] slice limitation to analyze all ChiNext stocks, or at least document this limitation clearly in the output file.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"issue\": \"Potential off-by-one error in 30-day high calculation: I use df.iloc[lookback_start:end_idx+1] which includes the low-volume period itself, but the task may expect the 30-day high to be calculated from a period before the pattern starts\",\n      \"severity\": \"low\",\n      \"affected_agents\": [\"claudecode\"],\n      \"recommendation\": \"Clarify whether the '30-day high' should include or exclude the low-volume period days. The current implementation includes them, which makes the breakout condition slightly easier to satisfy.\"\n    }\n  ],\n\n  \"update_plan\": {\n    \"should_update\": false,\n    \"rationale\": \"While Codex's implementation is more elegant with better pandas idioms and cleaner code structure, my solution is functionally correct and implements all required conditions accurately. The core algorithm logic is equivalent across all agents - we all found zero matching stocks, which suggests the issue is not with the implementation but rather with data availability or the inherent rarity of this pattern in the specified timeframe. Adopting Codex's code style improvements (vectorized operations, type hints, generator functions) would be nice-to-have refactoring but would not change the output results. Since the task is graded on correctness of logic a